<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n41038d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n41" href="#n41038d">N41 (VI.B.33)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n41all.htm#n41038d"> 38(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> takes absolutely</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">If a husband purchases property or makes investments with his own money in his wife&apos;s name or transfers any property to her, the wife <mark>takes it absolutely</mark>, unless there is proof that he intended her to hold it as trustee for him. <small> Maud I. Crofts, <a name="MICW" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#MICW"><cite title="source">Women under English Law</cite></a>, 1st ed. (1925) 36</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
